-HONEY, WE'RE HERE.
LET'S GO MEET YOUR NEW DADDY.

07:17.132 --> 07:18.002
THANKS.

07:21.528 --> 07:25.270
-[PEACEFUL PIANO MUSIC]

07:43.550 --> 07:44.420
-THIS WAY.

07:47.118 --> 07:48.119
-HOBIE: WHAT'S THE HURRY?

07:48.250 --> 07:49.251
-LESLIE: I'M EXCITED.

07:52.689 --> 07:54.430
-MAN: HEY,
HOW YOU DOING?
-HOBIE: HEY, WHAT'S UP.

07:54.561 --> 07:56.388
-MAN: ALL RIGHT,
I NEED YOU TO SIGN RIGHT HERE.

08:00.305 --> 08:01.481
OKAY, HERE'S YOUR HARNESS.

08:04.875 --> 08:05.659
ALRIGHT, THANKS.

08:05.789 --> 08:06.573
-LESLIE: HURRY UP.

08:07.443 --> 08:09.924
-OKAY. HERE YOU GO.

08:11.012 --> 08:11.882
-THANK YOU.

08:12.796 --> 08:13.841
-MAN: OKAY, HAVE FUN.

08:13.971 --> 08:14.972
-HOBIE: CLAIR, WAIT UP.

08:18.280 --> 08:19.847
-GOOD AFTERNOON,
BAYWATCH HEADQUARTERS.

08:19.977 --> 08:21.370
-MITCH: WHO IS THIS, RON?

08:21.501 --> 08:23.111
-HEY MITCH,
CALLING FROM ALASKA?

08:23.241 --> 08:24.199
-YEAH.

08:24.329 --> 08:25.113
-RON: HOW IS IT?

08:25.243 --> 08:26.897
-IT'S SPECTACULAR.

08:27.028 --> 08:28.290
-RON: HEY YOU
GUYS, IT'S MITCH.

08:28.420 --> 08:30.074
-LIFEGUARDS: HEY, MITCH.

08:30.205 --> 08:31.293
-THEY ALL SAY HI.

08:31.423 --> 08:33.337
-LISTEN TO ME. IS CRAIG AROUND?

08:33.469 --> 08:34.339
-RON: NO, HE'S OFF TODAY.

08:34.470 --> 08:35.993
ANYTHING I CAN DO?

08:36.124 --> 08:38.518
-I NEED YOU TO RUN
A POLICE CHECK ON TWO NAMES.

08:38.648 --> 08:40.910
PAUL NICHOLS AND LESLIE STRYKER.

08:41.520 --> 08:42.347
-LESLIE STRYKER?

08:42.477 --> 08:44.261
-YEAH. YOU KNOW HER?

08:45.220 --> 08:47.570
-ALL I KNOW IS THAT SHE'S
WANTED FOR ATTEMPTED MURDER.

08:48.658 --> 08:50.312
-ATTEMPTED MURDER?

08:50.442 --> 08:51.748
-SOMETHING TO DO WITH THE
GUY APRIL FOUND LAST WEEK.

08:54.359 --> 08:55.491
-THANKS.

08:57.014 --> 08:58.407
-WHAT'S WRONG, MITCH?

08:58.538 --> 08:59.800
-WHERE'S HOBIE?

08:59.930 --> 09:01.323
-WELL I SAW HIM ABOUT
AN HOUR AGO.

09:01.453 --> 09:02.672
HE SAID HE WAS GOING
PARAGLIDING WITH CLAIR.

09:02.803 --> 09:03.891
-AH, DAMN IT.

09:04.021 --> 09:05.545
ALL RIGHT, LOOK.

09:05.675 --> 09:06.763
IF YOU SEE THIS GAVIN GUY,
YOU STAY AWAY FROM HIM.

09:07.372 --> 09:08.635
YOU WANT TO SEE A GLACIER?

09:08.765 --> 09:09.984
WE'RE GONNA SEE A
GLACIER. COME ON.

09:10.114 --> 09:10.941
-CODY: WHAT'S UP?

09:11.638 --> 09:16.207
-[OMINOUS MUSIC]

09:21.691 --> 09:22.562
-MAN: HI, HOW ARE YOU?

09:23.171 --> 09:24.085
HEY, YOU WANT TO RENT?

09:24.215 --> 09:25.695
HEY, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

09:26.304 --> 09:27.567
-I'M GOING PARAGLIDING.

09:34.748 --> 09:39.491
-[MAJESTIC MUSIC]

10:19.053 --> 10:23.884
-[SINISTER MUSIC]

10:36.026 --> 10:37.158
-HOBIE: SOMEBODY'S
COMING AFTER US.

10:37.288 --> 10:39.203
WE GOTTA GO THE OTHER WAY.

10:39.813 --> 10:40.640
-LESLIE: NO!

10:59.397 --> 11:00.877
-CLAIR, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

11:01.530 --> 11:03.358
WE'RE HEADING AWAY
FROM THE SHIP.

11:05.229 --> 11:07.231
CLAIR, NO! NOT THAT WAY!

11:07.971 --> 11:10.626
-HOBIE, GO BACK TO
THE SHIP. JUST GO.

11:10.757 --> 11:13.890
-TURN LEFT. YOU'RE
GOING THE WRONG WAY.

11:23.987 --> 11:27.077
CLAIR, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING? THIS IS CRAZY.

11:27.208 --> 11:28.296
DO YOU KNOW THIS GUY?

11:28.426 --> 11:30.298
-HOBIE, LEAVE ME ALONE.

11:30.428 --> 11:32.126
JUST GO AWAY, DAMN IT!

11:41.918 --> 11:43.180
-HE'S SHOOTING AT US.

11:43.311 --> 11:44.747
[GUNFIRE]

11:45.879 --> 11:48.011
-LAND ON THE GLACIER, NOW!

11:48.142 --> 11:50.361
OR I SWEAR, THIS WILL
BE TARGET PRACTICE.

11:50.492 --> 11:51.623
-WHAT DID HE SAY?

11:51.754 --> 11:54.235
-LAND NOW, OR YOU'RE BOTH DEAD.

12:04.288 --> 12:06.160
THAT WAS YOUR LAST WARNING.

12:06.290 --> 12:07.857
-ALL RIGHT! OKAY!

12:07.988 --> 12:10.120
COME ON, HOBIE.
WE'D BETTER GO DOWN.

12:12.296 --> 12:16.779
-[TENSE MUSIC]

12:57.385 --> 12:58.299
-COME ON.

13:01.084 --> 13:02.216
WHAT'S GOING ON?

13:02.782 --> 13:03.957
-LESLIE: NO, COME ON. JUST GO.

13:07.612 --> 13:09.614
HURRY UP, HOBIE! HE'S COMING!

13:10.267 --> 13:15.229
-[EXCITING MUSIC]

13:33.943 --> 13:34.770
-GAVIN: LESLIE!

13:34.901 --> 13:36.076
-WHO IS THIS GUY?

13:36.206 --> 13:37.773
WHY IS HE AFTER YOU?

13:38.600 --> 13:39.949
WHY IS HE CALLING YOU LESLIE?

13:40.080 --> 13:41.081
-LESLIE: YOU
DON'T WANT TO KNOW.

13:41.211 --> 13:42.169
-HOBIE: YES, I DO.

13:47.827 --> 13:48.697
-DAMN IT.

13:53.484 --> 13:54.572
-LESLIE: COME ON!

14:01.666 --> 14:02.319
-HOBIE: COME ON.

14:09.022 --> 14:10.066
-LESLIE: COME ON, THIS WAY.

14:11.415 --> 14:16.377
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

15:29.841 --> 15:31.887
-HEAD TOWARDS THE
MENDENHALL GLACIER.

15:33.149 --> 15:33.976
-PILOT: ROGER THAT.

15:46.293 --> 15:49.513
-[ANXIOUS MUSIC]

15:57.521 --> 15:59.262
-HOBIE: KEEP GOING,
HE'S RIGHT ON OUR TAIL.

16:29.901 --> 16:31.468
-MITCH, I THINK WE GOT SOMETHING
OVER HERE.

16:34.428 --> 16:36.604
-ALL RIGHT, SET US DOWN
RIGHT BY THOSE CHUTES.

16:37.213 --> 16:38.649
-PILOT: ALL RIGHT,
SIR. SETTING HER DOWN.

16:54.926 --> 16:55.797
-CODY: HERE.

16:56.928 --> 16:57.799
-MITCH: ALL RIGHT.

16:59.583 --> 17:01.324
THANKS, THANKS!

17:12.291 --> 17:13.554
HOBIE!

17:15.643 --> 17:18.646
-CODY: MITCH, THE
TRACKS GO THIS WAY.

17:19.690 --> 17:20.560
-LET'S GO.

17:24.913 --> 17:26.045
HOBIE!

17:32.181 --> 17:34.923
[GUNFIRE]

17:37.578 --> 17:38.535
-RUN, THIS WAY.

17:38.666 --> 17:41.495
[SCREAMING]

17:48.241 --> 17:49.068
-YOU ALL RIGHT?

17:49.198 --> 17:50.373
-I'M FINE.

17:50.504 --> 17:51.200
HOW THE HELL DO WE
GET OUT OF HERE?

17:51.331 --> 17:52.245
-I DON'T KNOW.

17:53.289 --> 17:54.464
WE'RE IN AN ICE CAVE.

18:00.296 --> 18:03.865
-[CHUCKLING] LOOKS A LITTLE
COLD DOWN THERE, LESLIE.

18:04.474 --> 18:05.867
ALL RIGHT, HERE'S THE DEAL.

18:06.476 --> 18:08.913
IF YOU AND JUNIOR WANT TO
GET OUT OF THERE ALIVE,

18:09.044 --> 18:12.308
TAKE OFF THAT BACKPACK,
UNDO THE STRAPS,

18:12.439 --> 18:14.267
TOSS IT UP HERE,
I'LL LOWER IT DOWN,

18:15.094 --> 18:16.182
AND PULL YOU BOTH OUT.

18:16.791 --> 18:18.575
-LIKE I BELIEVE YOU.

18:18.706 --> 18:20.534
-OH RIGHT, WELL YOU CAN STAY
DOWN THERE AND FREEZE TO DEATH

18:20.664 --> 18:22.057
FOR ALL I CARE.

18:22.188 --> 18:24.015
EITHER WAY, I'M NOT
LEAVING THIS GLACIER

18:24.146 --> 18:25.060
WITHOUT MY EMERALDS.

18:26.279 --> 18:29.630
-JUST TAKE OFF THE BACKPACK
AND THROW HIM THE STRAPS, NOW.

18:30.239 --> 18:32.894
-COME ON, LESLIE,
JUNIOR'S THINKING RIGHT.

18:33.590 --> 18:34.852
HE'S NOT AS DUMB AS HE LOOKS.

18:34.983 --> 18:37.594
SORRY SWEETHEART, GAME'S OVER.

18:38.943 --> 18:39.857
YOU LOSE.

18:50.477 --> 18:51.695
THAT A GIRL.

18:52.827 --> 18:53.697
-HOBIE: ALL RIGHT.

18:54.742 --> 18:57.701
-TOSS IT. COME ON, YOU
CAN DO BETTER THAN THAT.

18:57.832 --> 18:58.702
THROW IT.

19:01.096 --> 19:02.750
ALL RIGHT, I GOT YOU.

19:07.189 --> 19:08.234
BYE.

19:13.064 --> 19:15.110
-SEE, HE HAS NO
INTENTION OF HELPING US.

19:15.241 --> 19:16.111
-WHO ARE YOU?

19:16.242 --> 19:17.243
-WHAT DOES IT MATTER?

19:17.373 --> 19:18.592
-GAVIN: WHAT THE HELL IS THIS?

19:23.205 --> 19:24.293
WHERE ARE MY EMERALDS?

19:27.166 --> 19:28.167
-THEY'RE RIGHT HERE.

19:29.080 --> 19:31.953
YOU WANT 'EM, YOU
COME AND GET 'EM.

19:34.085 --> 19:34.912
-YOU TOSS THEM UP HERE.

19:35.609 --> 19:37.176
AND YOU DO IT, NOW!

19:37.785 --> 19:38.742
-JUST LET US OUT
OF HERE, ALL RIGHT?

20:01.722 --> 20:02.592
-ALL RIGHT.

20:03.898 --> 20:05.726
NOW YOU'VE GOT THREE
TO TOSS THEM UP.

20:06.553 --> 20:07.554
AND THAT WAS ONE.

20:08.294 --> 20:10.818
THEY CALL AN ICE AVALANCHE,
"WHITE THUNDER."

20:10.948 --> 20:13.386
AND THAT'S EXACTLY WHAT
YOU'RE GONNA BE BURIED IN

20:13.516 --> 20:15.083
IF YOU DON'T GIVE
ME MY EMERALDS.

20:15.214 --> 20:17.694
AND BELIEVE ME, I DON'T
MIND DOING A LITTLE DIGGING

20:17.825 --> 20:18.913
TO GET WHAT I WANT.

20:19.522 --> 20:21.045
-GIVE ME THEM.
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

20:21.176 --> 20:22.960
-THEY'RE NOT WORTH
GETTING KILLED FOR.

20:23.091 --> 20:24.745
-WE'RE GONNA DIE EITHER WAY.

20:24.875 --> 20:27.791
-YOU THROW THEM UP,
AND I GIVE YOU MY WORD

20:27.922 --> 20:29.184
I WILL PULL YOU BOTH OUT.

20:29.315 --> 20:30.446
-NO, YOU CAN'T TRUST HIM!

20:30.577 --> 20:31.926
-I CAN'T TRUST YOU.

20:32.579 --> 20:33.710
-COME ON, TOSS THEM UP.

20:33.841 --> 20:34.842
-CATCH.

20:34.972 --> 20:36.191
-LESLIE: NO!

20:44.460 --> 20:45.635
-HAND THEM OVER.

20:46.680 --> 20:47.550
DO IT.

20:49.987 --> 20:51.380
DO IT!

20:59.780 --> 21:02.130
YOU EVER SEEN WHAT FIVE MILLION
DOLLARS LOOKS LIKE, KID?

21:02.913 --> 21:03.914
FEAST YOUR EYES.

21:04.959 --> 21:06.700
-AS FAR AS I'M CONCERNED,
YOU CAN TAKE THOSE EMERALDS

21:06.830 --> 21:08.267
AND SHOVE THEM--
-HEY, HEY, HEY.

21:08.397 --> 21:10.269
YOU MIND YOUR MANNERS
THERE, JUNIOR.

21:11.792 --> 21:13.663
IT'S NOT MY FAULT SHE
SUCKERED YOU INTO THIS.

21:13.794 --> 21:15.970
I DO UNDERSTAND THE
ATTRACTION, HUH.

21:16.579 --> 21:19.713
IT'S NOT EVERYDAY YOU COME
ACROSS A COLD-BLOODED KILLER

21:19.843 --> 21:21.541
WITH SUCH WARMTH AND CHARM.

21:23.717 --> 21:25.501
TOO BAD YOU HAD TO BE SO GREEDY.

21:27.590 --> 21:28.765
-YOU KILLED SOMEONE?

21:28.896 --> 21:30.245
-WELL SHE TRIED.

21:30.811 --> 21:32.682
SHE CAME PRETTY DAMN CLOSE, TOO.

21:32.813 --> 21:34.293
BUT ROBBIE CAME OUT OF THE COMA.

21:38.906 --> 21:40.647
-I'M GONNA KILL THAT GIRL
AND HIM.

21:49.395 --> 21:50.831
-HOBIE!

21:53.616 --> 21:54.487
-HOBIE?

21:58.708 --> 22:00.449
-HOBIE: I'D LIKE
SOME ANSWERS HERE.

22:02.886 --> 22:04.279
WHAT'S THIS ALL ABOUT?

22:04.888 --> 22:07.064
-MY ASSOCIATE AND I HIRED
MISS STRYKER AND HER PARTNER

22:07.195 --> 22:08.718
TO RETRIEVE OUR EMERALDS.

22:08.849 --> 22:09.937
-YOUR EMERALDS?

22:10.067 --> 22:11.634
WHO DID YOU STEAL THEM FROM?

22:12.243 --> 22:15.029
-YOU KNOW I DON'T REALLY SEE
HOW THAT'S RELEVANT RIGHT NOW.

22:15.159 --> 22:16.683
SEE, WE HAVE A MUCH
BIGGER PROBLEM.

22:16.813 --> 22:19.338
WE'RE ALL GOING TO
DIE FROM HYPOTHERMIA.

22:19.947 --> 22:21.949
AND WHAT EVER MADE YOU THINK
YOU COULD GET AWAY WITH THIS?

22:23.733 --> 22:24.995
-MITCH: HOBIE?

22:25.126 --> 22:26.170
-THAT'S MY DAD. DAD!

22:26.301 --> 22:28.172
DAD! WE'RE DOWN HERE!

22:28.782 --> 22:29.826
DAD!

22:30.697 --> 22:31.828
DAD, SAVE US!

22:35.528 --> 22:37.617
WE'RE DOWN HERE, IN THE CAVE!

22:41.272 --> 22:43.362
-THROW DOWN THE ROPE, NOW.

22:47.191 --> 22:48.715
-TOSS UP THE GUN FIRST.

22:48.845 --> 22:51.326
-DO I APPEAR TO BE IN
THE MOOD TO NEGOTIATE?

22:51.457 --> 22:53.937
-CODY: YOU'LL NEVER GET OFF
THIS GLACIER WITHOUT OUR HELP.

22:54.068 --> 22:56.810
-THREE, TWO--

22:56.940 --> 22:58.638
-ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT, ALL
RIGHT. JUST TAKE IT EASY.

23:02.163 --> 23:03.120
THROW DOWN THE ROPE.

23:15.394 --> 23:17.091
-GAVIN: HOPE YOU LEARNED
YOUR LESSON, SWEETHEART.

23:17.221 --> 23:19.310
-WHY DON'T YOU TIE
THAT AROUND YOUR NECK?

23:19.441 --> 23:20.747
-OH, THAT'S REALLY CUTE.

23:20.877 --> 23:23.053
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT,
I'M SICK OF YOU--

24:34.081 --> 24:35.343
-I'LL TAKE THESE.

24:40.348 --> 24:43.438
CODY, GET US THE
HELL OUT OF HERE.

24:44.134 --> 24:45.614
BEFORE THIS THING COLLAPSES.

24:54.231 --> 24:56.407
HE'S ALL YOURS. GET
HIM OUT OF HERE.

24:56.538 --> 24:57.539
-WE'LL TAKE THEM TO
THE STATE TROOPERS.

24:57.670 --> 24:58.497
THEY'RE WAITING FOR THEM BELOW.

24:58.627 --> 25:00.020
-HAVE A NICE FLIGHT.

25:00.673 --> 25:01.500
-HOLD ON.

25:03.023 --> 25:04.677
WAS ANYTHING YOU SAID TRUE?

25:06.374 --> 25:07.375
-JUST GET US THE
HELL OUT OF HERE

25:07.506 --> 25:08.550
BEFORE WE FREEZE TO DEATH.

25:11.684 --> 25:14.774
-OFFICER: ALL RIGHT,
WATCH YOUR HEAD.

25:15.557 --> 25:17.559
-COME ON. IT'S OVER.

25:18.168 --> 25:19.518
LET'S GET BACK TO THE SHIP.

25:25.349 --> 25:27.351
-CODY: HOBE, YOU SURE
KNOW HOW TO PICK 'EM.

25:48.503 --> 25:49.809
-HI.
-HI, ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

25:49.939 --> 25:51.550
-YEAH, I'M FINE.
-HOBIE AND THE GLACIER?

25:51.680 --> 25:52.942
-HE'S FINE, I'M FINE.
BUT ANYHOW, I'LL EXPLAIN LATER.

25:53.073 --> 25:54.291
WHAT HAPPENED WITH PETER?

25:57.947 --> 25:58.992
-PETER'S MARRIED.

26:01.777 --> 26:02.648
-WHAT?

26:11.221 --> 26:12.222
PETER'S MARRIED?

26:14.660 --> 26:15.791
-YEAH.

26:16.400 --> 26:19.229
I MET HIS WIFE AND
THEIR BABY BOY.

26:20.753 --> 26:22.058
-YOU'VE GOTTA BE KIDDING ME.

26:23.320 --> 26:27.803
-NO, SO OBVIOUSLY WE'LL NOT
BE GETTING BACK TOGETHER.

26:28.717 --> 26:30.850
I MEAN, HE'LL VISIT
ASHLEY WHEN HE CAN,

26:30.980 --> 26:35.245
BUT FOR THE MOST PART,
WE'RE ON OUR OWN.

26:36.638 --> 26:37.987
-ARE YOU ALL RIGHT
WITH ALL THIS?

26:40.816 --> 26:44.472
-TO BE HONEST WITH
YOU, IT'S A HUGE RELIEF.

26:45.734 --> 26:48.476
I MEAN, I KNEW IN MY
HEART IT WOULD NEVER WORK.

26:49.956 --> 26:51.914
HOW CAN YOU MARRY SOMEONE
WHEN YOU'RE IN LOVE

26:52.045 --> 26:54.395
WITH SOMEONE ELSE?

26:56.353 --> 27:00.488
THE QUESTION IS, I DON'T
KNOW IF HE'S IN LOVE WITH ME.

27:06.059 --> 27:08.757
-WHO'S HE?

27:11.020 --> 27:11.891
-YOU.

27:13.980 --> 27:14.807
-ME?

27:17.810 --> 27:18.724
-ARE YOU?

27:19.725 --> 27:21.117
-AM I WHAT?

27:23.119 --> 27:24.294
-ARE YOU IN LOVE WITH ME?

27:26.993 --> 27:28.124
-AM I IN LOVE WITH YOU?

27:28.777 --> 27:29.604
-YEAH.

27:32.041 --> 27:36.350
-NEELY, I LOVE YOU MORE THAN
ANYONE ON THIS EARTH.

27:51.452 --> 27:54.498
I DIDN'T KNOW. I DIDN'T KNOW.
WHY DIDN'T YOU SAY SOMETHING?

27:55.761 --> 27:57.719
I WAS SO UPSET, I THOUGHT--

28:04.030 --> 28:08.251
-[PLEASANT MUSIC]

28:08.382 --> 28:11.298
IT'S GOTTA BE ABOUT THE MOST
MAGNIFICENT PLACE
IN THE WORLD, HUH?

28:12.647 --> 28:14.170
HOW YOU HOLDING UP?

28:14.301 --> 28:16.390
-ALL RIGHT, CONSIDERING
I FEEL LIKE A TOTAL IDIOT.

28:16.520 --> 28:18.174
-AH, COME HERE. COME HERE. LOOK.

28:18.827 --> 28:23.049
EVERYBODY MAKES MISTAKES, I
MEAN, NOT QUITE ON THE SCALE

28:23.179 --> 28:26.705
OF THAT ONE.
BUT HEY, WE'RE IN
ALASKA. EVERYTHING'S BIG.

28:26.835 --> 28:27.706
-YEAH.

28:28.271 --> 28:29.882
DAD, I'M SORRY
I WAS SUCH A JERK.

28:30.012 --> 28:31.448
IF I WOULD'VE JUST
LISTENED TO YOU,

28:31.579 --> 28:32.841
NONE OF THIS WOULD'VE HAPPENED.

28:33.363 --> 28:36.149
ONCE AGAIN, I PROVE THAT
FATHER KNOWS BEST, RIGHT?

28:36.279 --> 28:38.717
-WELL, THE WAY I LOOK AT IT,
IF IT WEREN'T FOR YOU,

28:38.847 --> 28:40.544
WE WOULDN'T BE UP
HERE TO SEE ALL THIS.

28:41.110 --> 28:42.677
SO CONSIDER IT EVEN.

28:43.634 --> 28:44.984
-YOU MEAN THAT?

28:45.114 --> 28:46.420
-YEAH I MEAN THAT,
BUT NEXT TIME THINK.

28:46.550 --> 28:47.769
YOU KNOW?
JUST LOOK BEFORE YOU LEAP.

28:48.335 --> 28:50.772
ESPECIALLY WHEN IT COMES
TO THE OPPOSITE SEX.

28:51.512 --> 28:53.166
-BELIEVE ME,
I'VE LEARNED THAT LESSON.

28:53.296 --> 28:56.299
I DECIDED ALREADY, I'M NOT
DATING AGAIN UNTIL COLLEGE.

28:56.430 --> 28:57.692
-THAT'S NEXT MONTH.

28:58.606 --> 29:00.216
-YOU'RE RIGHT, I PROBABLY
CAN'T WAIT THAT LONG.

29:01.957 --> 29:03.959
-OH, BY THE WAY, YOU'VE
GOT YOUR TUX, RIGHT?

29:04.090 --> 29:08.094
-YEAH.
-GOOD, I NEED A BEST MAN.

29:08.224 --> 29:09.617
-WHAT?

29:09.748 --> 29:11.532
-I NEED YOU TO BE MY BEST MAN.

29:11.662 --> 29:12.838
I MAY BE GETTING
MARRIED TOMORROW.

29:13.403 --> 29:14.665
-YOU'RE GETTING MARRIED?

29:14.796 --> 29:16.276
-YEAH.
-TO WHO?

29:16.406 --> 29:17.451
-WHO DO YOU THINK?

29:17.581 --> 29:19.105
-NEELY?
-NEELY.

29:20.846 --> 29:22.282
-DAD, WAY TO GO.

29:22.412 --> 29:24.763
-HEY LISTEN, I GOTTA
SHOW YOU SOMETHING.

29:24.893 --> 29:28.027
LOOK AT THIS. IS THAT AWESOME?

29:28.157 --> 29:29.593
TWO MONTHS SALARY.

29:29.724 --> 29:30.943
-AMAZING.

29:31.508 --> 29:32.292
-HEY.

29:32.422 --> 29:33.728
-MITCH.
-YEAH?

29:33.859 --> 29:35.904
-RAN INTO A LITTLE HITCH
IN YOUR PLAN.

29:36.513 --> 29:38.124
WE CAN'T FIND THE
CAPTAIN, HE'S OFF THE SHIP
WITH THE COAST
GUARD OR SOMETHING.

29:38.254 --> 29:40.909
BUT I DID MANAGE TO FIND
THE ONLY MINISTER ON BOARD.

29:41.040 --> 29:42.302
-ACTUALLY, I'M A RABBI.

29:42.432 --> 29:44.130
-A RABBI?

29:44.957 --> 29:47.307
-WHEN YOU'RE IN LOVE, WHAT
DIFFERENCE DOES IT MAKE?

29:47.916 --> 29:49.570
-DO EITHER YOU OR THE
BRIDE SPEAK HEBREW?

29:50.310 --> 29:52.747
-NO, WE'RE NOT EVEN JEWISH. NO.

29:52.878 --> 29:54.314
-YOU'RE NOT JEWISH?
YOU LOOK JEWISH.

29:54.444 --> 29:55.489
-WELL, I, NO, WE'RE NOT--

29:56.925 --> 29:59.667
WOULD YOU DO ME A FAVOR?
FIND THE CAPTAIN.

30:07.631 --> 30:08.763
-HEY.

30:10.547 --> 30:11.505
LOOK AT THE VIEW.

30:12.549 --> 30:13.376
-WOW.

30:13.507 --> 30:15.770
WOW, THAT'S AMAZING.

30:16.336 --> 30:18.294
-GLACIER BAY IS SO PEACEFUL.

30:18.860 --> 30:21.384
AND I WAS THINKING, IF I EVER
GOT MARRIED AGAIN,

30:21.515 --> 30:23.647
I WOULD LOVE TO TAKE
A HONEYMOON HERE.

30:24.605 --> 30:26.041
-REALLY?
-YEAH.

30:26.737 --> 30:30.089
-WELL, IT'S FUNNY THAT
YOU SHOULD MENTION THAT.

30:32.656 --> 30:34.702
I MEAN, I WAS WALKING
AROUND THE SHIP.

30:34.833 --> 30:36.660
WELL, I PASSED
THIS JEWELRY STORE,

30:36.791 --> 30:39.489
AND IT JUST KIND OF
OCCURRED TO ME THAT, WELL,

30:39.620 --> 30:42.188
THERE WAS THIS QUESTION
THAT I FORGOT TO ASK YOU.

30:43.450 --> 30:44.320
-WHAT?

30:52.198 --> 30:53.112
-WILL YOU MARRY ME?

30:54.287 --> 30:56.376
-MITCH, I DON'T
KNOW WHAT TO SAY.

30:56.506 --> 30:58.726
-SAY YES. SAY YES.

31:00.815 --> 31:01.598
-YES!

31:01.729 --> 31:02.817
-YES?
-YES!

31:02.948 --> 31:04.036
-MITCH: YES, YES!

31:05.864 --> 31:07.387
HANG ON, HANG ON. I
ALMOST DROPPED IT.

31:07.517 --> 31:09.171
I GOT IT, I GOT IT,
JUST KIDDING. JUST KIDDING.

31:14.220 --> 31:16.962
-NEELY: OH GOD,
IT IS BEAUTIFUL.

31:17.092 --> 31:19.225
ABSOLUTELY BEAUTIFUL.

31:25.927 --> 31:30.889
-[TRANQUIL MUSIC]

31:46.208 --> 31:49.168
-DONNA: HEY NEELY. LOOK
AT THIS VIEW, WOULD YOU?

31:49.298 --> 31:50.996
HI, ISN'T IT BEAUTIFUL HERE?

31:51.126 --> 31:52.388
-NEELY: IT'S GORGEOUS.

31:52.519 --> 31:53.172
-DONNA: I JUST
SAW HUMPBACK WHALES.

31:53.302 --> 31:54.129
-WOW.

31:54.782 --> 31:56.175
LOOK.

31:56.305 --> 31:57.437
-DONNA: OH MY GOD!
I KNOW, HOBIE TOLD ME.

31:57.567 --> 31:58.786
CONGRATULATIONS.

31:58.917 --> 32:00.483
-THANK YOU.

32:00.614 --> 32:02.921
YOU KNOW, I WAS HOPING
YOU'D BE MY MAID OF HONOR.

32:03.617 --> 32:05.010
-REALLY?
-YEAH.

32:05.140 --> 32:06.489
YOU KNOW, YOU'VE ALWAYS
BEEN THERE FOR ME.

32:06.620 --> 32:08.709
WITHOUT YOU, I DON'T KNOW
WHERE I'D BE.

32:08.839 --> 32:10.667
-WELL, NOT ALASKA,
THAT'S FOR SURE.

32:10.798 --> 32:13.540
NEELY, CONGRATULATIONS.
I'M SO HAPPY FOR YOU.

32:13.670 --> 32:14.541
-THANK YOU, DONNA.

32:15.368 --> 32:20.329
-[ORNATE ORCHESTRAL MUSIC]

33:00.152 --> 33:01.849
[HUSHED WHISPERING]

33:57.687 --> 33:58.819
-GOOD JOB.

33:59.472 --> 34:02.040
-WE HAVE COME TOGETHER
TODAY TO WITNESS THE JOINING

34:02.170 --> 34:05.695
OF THIS MAN AND THIS WOMAN
IN HOLY MATRIMONY.

34:06.696 --> 34:08.610
IF ANYONE HERE
OBJECTS TO THE JOINING

34:08.742 --> 34:11.745
OF THESE TWO SOULS AS ONE,
LET THEM SPEAK NOW

34:12.311 --> 34:14.181
OR FOREVER HOLD THEIR PEACE.

34:15.226 --> 34:19.056
MITCH AND NEELY HAVE DECIDED
TO EXCHANGE VOWS OF THEIR OWN.

34:19.753 --> 34:20.623
MITCH.

34:25.976 --> 34:31.851
NEELY, I PROMISE TO LOVE YOU,
TO HONOR YOU,

34:33.158 --> 34:34.681
AND TO ALWAYS BE THERE FOR YOU.

34:36.335 --> 34:41.079
I PLEDGE WITH ALL MY HEART
TO BE A GOOD HUSBAND,

34:42.384 --> 34:46.431
A GOOD FRIEND,
AND A GOOD FATHER.

34:52.829 --> 34:56.311
-AND I PROMISE TO TRUST IN YOU

34:57.486 --> 35:03.449
AS A FRIEND, AS A PARTNER,
AND AS MY TRUE LOVE.

35:04.798 --> 35:06.626
I PROMISE TO ALWAYS BE WITH YOU

35:06.756 --> 35:08.323
IN GOOD TIMES AND IN BAD.

35:09.977 --> 35:15.896
AND I VOW, WITH ALL MY
HEART, TO BE A GOOD MOTHER

35:16.679 --> 35:18.028
AND A GOOD WIFE.

35:25.079 --> 35:26.646
-THE RINGS, PLEASE.

35:31.041 --> 35:32.260
-MITCH: THANKS, PAL.

35:41.226 --> 35:42.096
THIS RING.

35:45.055 --> 35:45.926
